**Charlene Amoia** is an American actress best known for her role as Wendy the
waitress in the TV sitcom _[How I Met Your Mother](/wiki/How_I_Met_Your_Mother
"How I Met Your Mother")_.[1] Some of her other television credits include
_[Glee](/wiki/Glee_\(TV_series\) "Glee \(TV series\)")_ and Diana Coto on
_[Switched at Birth](/wiki/Switched_at_Birth_\(TV_series\) "Switched at Birth
\(TV series\)")_ , and her film credits include Kevin's ([Thomas Ian
Nicholas](/wiki/Thomas_Ian_Nicholas "Thomas Ian Nicholas")) wife Elllie in
_[American Reunion](/wiki/American_Reunion "American Reunion")_ (2012) from
the [_American Pie_ series](/wiki/American_Pie_\(series\) "American Pie
\(series\)").

## Childhood and early
career[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Charlene_Amoia&action=edit&section=1&editintro=Template:BLP_editintro
"Edit section: Childhood and early career")]

Charlene was born in Buffalo New York. She got her start in modeling[2] before
making the transition to acting in 2001 with a role on the soap opera, _[Port
Charles](/wiki/Port_Charles "Port Charles")_. That part on the daytime drama
led to guest appearances in several other series, including
_[Joey](/wiki/Joey_\(TV_series\) "Joey \(TV series\)")_ ,
_[Girlfriends](/wiki/Girlfriends_\(U.S._TV_series\) "Girlfriends \(U.S. TV
series\)")_ , _[90210](/wiki/90210_\(TV_Series\) "90210 \(TV Series\)")_ , and
as Anna Schick in _[The Young and the
Restless](/wiki/The_Young_and_the_Restless "The Young and the Restless")._

##
Career[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Charlene_Amoia&action=edit&section=2&editintro=Template:BLP_editintro
"Edit section: Career")]

### _How I Met Your
Mother_[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Charlene_Amoia&action=edit&section=3&editintro=Template:BLP_editintro
"Edit section: How I Met Your Mother")]

From 2005 to 2011, she played Wendy, a waitress that works at the bar, the
main setting of the American TV hit _[How I Met Your
Mother](/wiki/How_I_Met_Your_Mother "How I Met Your Mother")_.[3] Although at
times on the series she was rumored to be Ted's future wife,[4] Amoia herself
didn't believe Wendy would turn out to be "the one". "Wendy had sex with
Barney behind the bar on the show and also made out with Ted’s dad, so the
likelihood of this character being the mom, I thought, was pretty small
anyway, but the fact that fans were rooting for me was awesome!" the actress
has said. [5] On playing Wendy, she has said, "I love playing flawed
characters. Wendy is so genuinely sweet and guileless to a point that she
doesn’t realize she’s being taken advantage of. Being able to take on these
characteristics in a way that is funny and harmless is always so much fun!"[6]

### _American
Reunion_[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Charlene_Amoia&action=edit&section=4&editintro=Template:BLP_editintro
"Edit section: American Reunion")]

Amoia played Ellie, Kevin ([Thomas Ian Nicholas](/wiki/Thomas_Ian_Nicholas
"Thomas Ian Nicholas"))'s wife, in the fourth [_American
Pie_](/wiki/American_Pie_\(series\) "American Pie \(series\)") film, released
in 2012.[7] She originally auditioned for a different role before landing this
role.[8]

### Other TV and film
work[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Charlene_Amoia&action=edit&section=5&editintro=Template:BLP_editintro
"Edit section: Other TV and film work")]

Amoia also played Nurse Katie on daytime soap _[Days of Our
Lives](/wiki/Days_of_Our_Lives "Days of Our Lives")_ , Bailey on
[_Glee_](/wiki/Glee_\(TV_series\) "Glee \(TV series\)") and Diana Cotto on
[_Switched at Birth_](/wiki/Switched_at_Birth_\(TV_series\) "Switched at Birth
\(TV series\)"). Additionally she appeared in the TV series
_[90210](/wiki/90210_\(TV_Series\) "90210 \(TV Series\)")_ as teacher Miss
Wells in Season 1, Episode 7.

She has appeared in such films as _[Seven Pounds](/wiki/Seven_Pounds "Seven
Pounds")_ , with [Will Smith](/wiki/Will_Smith "Will Smith"), and _[American
Reunion](/wiki/American_Reunion "American Reunion")._ In 2013, she plays Jill
in _Fat_ , which premiered at the [Toronto International Film
Festival](/wiki/Toronto_International_Film_Festival "Toronto International
Film Festival").[9]

She recently guest starred on the show _[NCIS: New
Orleans](/wiki/NCIS:_New_Orleans "NCIS: New Orleans")_ as Carly Dawson in the
episode "[Breaking Brig](/wiki/Breaking_Brig "Breaking Brig")" and Kelly Press
on _[Major Crimes](/wiki/Major_Crimes "Major Crimes")_.

She played: Janet Conrad, a pushy [NATO](/wiki/NATO "NATO")
[Photographer](/wiki/Photographer "Photographer") who was seeking a career
changing "Front Line Photo" in the 2016 movie; _[Sniper: Special
Ops](/wiki/Sniper:_Special_Ops "Sniper: Special Ops")_.

In 2017 she appeared on _[American Horror Story](/wiki/American_Horror_Story
"American Horror Story")_ on the episode "[Great
Again](/wiki/Great_Again_\(American_Horror_Story\) "Great Again \(American
Horror Story\)")". In [season 14](/wiki/Grey%27s_Anatomy_\(season_14\) "Grey's
Anatomy \(season 14\)") of _[Grey's Anatomy](/wiki/Grey%27s_Anatomy "Grey's
Anatomy")_ she appeared as Dr. Kate Lachman.
